Aleph Package Manager
---------------------
Usage:
    %CMD% <subcommand> [options]

Subcommands:
    help, --help                                            Shows this help message and exits.
    version, --version, -v, -?                              Shows version information.
    install, add [--pretend] <package1 package2 ...>        Installs the specified packages.
                                                            --pretend disables filesystem actions.
    uninstall, remove [--pretend,--purge] <package1 package2 ...>     Removes the specified packages.
                                                            --purge removes all cached package files
    query [--desc,--regex] <term>                           Searches through all installed packages.
                                                            --desc outputs the package description.
                                                            --regex enables regex support.
    search [--desc,--regex] <term>                          Searches through all packages from
                                                            all available repositories using the
                                                            local database.
                                                            --desc outputs the package description.
                                                            --regex enables regex support.
    files <package>                                         List files of a package.
    list [--repo]                                           Lists all installed packages.
                                                            --repo lists all packages from
                                                                   all available repositories
                                                                   using the local database.

Examples:
    ./aleph install example-package1 example-package2
    ./aleph remove --purge example-package1
    ./aleph search --regex example.*?
    ./aleph list

For detailed documentation, visit: <https://github.com/ico277/aleph>
